 but is more specifically focused on clausal complements: the reader will find detailed discussions of finite and infinitival argument clauses, complex verb constructions and verb clustering. Volume 3 concludes with a description of adverbial modification and the overall structure of clauses in relation to, e.g., word order (verb placement, wh-movement. extraposition phenomena, scrambling, etc.).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLanguage and Literature. 4aLinguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aDutch, syntax, verbs.1 aCorver, Norbert, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVos, Riet, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066278808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311102376240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048524822?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048524822zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048524822/original  a978-3-11-066278-8 Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  a978-3-11-102376-2 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA